	<div id="footer_container">
		<div id="footer">
			<div id="licenses">
			<h3>A bit about Licenses</h3>
			<p>
				Publishing digital art is like going to a rooftop and tearing open a feather pillow. Can you control where the feathers go? Can you gather them all again? So it is with digital art.
			</p>
			<p>
				We can't control who copies our art, nor how they use it. Yet, we can at least ask those who find the feathers to think of us. To that end Six Minute Story empowers writers to license their work under six <a href="http://creativecommons.org">Creative Commons</a> licenses or to the Public Domain.
			</p> 
		
			</div>
		
			<div id="how_to_contact">
				<h3>If you want to tell us something</h3>
				<p>
				I like to hear from people who enjoy what I create. I also appreciate constructive criticism and suggestions for improvements. If your suggestion is feasible, I'll consider it and attempt to implement it. 
				</p>
				<p>
				You can get in touch with me via <a href="http://twitter.com/6minutestory">twitter</a>, Six Minute Story's <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Six-Minute-Story/177100150707">Facebook profile</a> or plain old email @ galen at six minute story dot com.
				</p>
		</div>
			<div class="clear">
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	
